The 2022 edition of the BET Awards was held in California earlier in the week and one of the attendees was Nigeria’s new sensation, Adaorah. Adaorah was spotted at both the BET most influential black people event and the award ceremony. In a brief chat, the “Rock My Borry” singer could not hide her excitement as Tems was announced the winner in one of the category awards.   Edochie’s first wife shrugs off marriage drama     Faze, Konga, others thrill at Ruggedman’s Foundation night     Paul & CeeCee Oniya’s group release Yoruba is my…   According to her, the Nigerian women folks are blazing strong and making the African continent proud. “I am proud of Tems and other Nigerians who were big winners at the BET awards. Over the years, we have proven our ability to stand tall musically and change the narrative with Afrobeats,” she said. The music sensation used the medium to announce her forthcoming single and her Nigerian media tour in July 2022”